      "justification_correct": "Domestic concerns, which include U.S. citizens, nationals, residents, and businesses organized under U.S. law, are subject to FCPA jurisdiction for their conduct anywhere in the world, even if no use of U.S. interstate commerce occurs.",
      "justification_wrong": "Foreign officials are recipients of bribes, not covered persons. Instrumentalities are entities that may employ foreign officials. Foreign subsidiaries are only covered when they act as agents of U.S. parents or when their conduct involves U.S. territory or interstate commerce.",
